'From Squeak3.6alpha of ''17 March 2003'' [latest update: #5278] on 27 June 2003 at 10:56:22 am'!"Change Set:		DeadServerFix-nkDate:			27 June 2003Author:			Ned KonzThis changeset fixes the problem that occurs when DeadServer contains a nil (which it can depending on when it gets set)."!!Utilities class methodsFor: 'fetching updates' stamp: 'nk 6/26/2003 21:12'!serverUrls 	"Return the current list of server URLs.  For code updates.  Format of UpdateUrlLists is #( ('squeak updates' ('url1' 'url2'))    ('some other updates' ('url3' 'url4')))"	| list |	list _ UpdateUrlLists first last.	"If there is a dead server, return a copy with that server last" 	Socket deadServer ifNotNil: [		list clone withIndexDo: [:aName :ind |		(aName beginsWith: Socket deadServer) ifTrue: [			list _ list asOrderedCollection.	"and it's a copy"			list removeAt: ind.			list addLast: aName]]	].	^ list asArray! !